HEADWORD: space sickness
<hw>space" sick`ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a group of symptoms,
prominently nausea, but sometimes including lethargy, headache, and
sweating, occuring under the weightless conditions of space
flight.</def> <au>[RHUD]</au>⟦br⟧
